#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.29:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.29:0.2"
msgid "3. Puggalavagga "
msgstr "3. Persons "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.29:0.3"
msgid "29. Andhasutta "
msgstr "29. Blind "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.129, sc1
msgctxt "an3.29:1.1"
msgid "“Tayome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“These three kinds of people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an3.29:1.2"
msgid "Katame tayo? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.29:1.3"
msgid "Andho, ekacakkhu, dvicakkhu. "
msgstr "The blind, the one-eyed, and the two-eyed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.29:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo andho? "
msgstr "Who is the blind person? "

#. VAR: phātiṃ kareyya → phātikareyya (bj)
msgctxt "an3.29:1.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tathārūpaṃ cakkhu na hoti yathārūpena cakkhunā anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigaccheyya adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ kareyya; "
msgstr "It’s someone who doesn’t have the kind of vision that’s needed to acquire more wealth or to increase the wealth they’ve already acquired. "

msgctxt "an3.29:1.6"
msgid "tathārūpampissa cakkhu na hoti yathārūpena cakkhunā kusalākusale dhamme jāneyya, sāvajjānavajje dhamme jāneyya, hīnappaṇīte dhamme jāneyya, kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāge dhamme jāneyya. "
msgstr "Nor do they have the kind of vision that’s needed to know the difference between qualities that are skillful and unskillful, blameworthy and blameless, inferior and superior, and those on the side of dark and bright. "

msgctxt "an3.29:1.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo andho. "
msgstr "This is called a blind person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.29:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo ekacakkhu? "
msgstr "Who is the person with one eye? "

#. VAR: phātiṃ kareyya → phāti kareyya (bj)
msgctxt "an3.29:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tathārūpaṃ cakkhu hoti yathārūpena cakkhunā anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigaccheyya adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ kareyya; "
msgstr "It’s someone who has the kind of vision that’s needed to acquire more wealth and to increase the wealth they’ve already acquired. "

#. VAR: tathārūpaṃ panassa → tathārūpampissa (bj, s2, s3, km, pts1, mr) | tathārūpassa (s1)
msgctxt "an3.29:2.3"
msgid "tathārūpaṃ panassa cakkhu na hoti yathārūpena cakkhunā kusalākusale dhamme jāneyya, sāvajjānavajje dhamme jāneyya, hīnappaṇīte dhamme jāneyya, kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāge dhamme jāneyya. "
msgstr "But they don’t have the kind of vision that’s needed to know the difference between qualities that are skillful and unskillful, blameworthy and blameless, inferior and superior, and those on the side of dark and bright. "

msgctxt "an3.29:2.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo ekacakkhu. "
msgstr "This is called a one-eyed person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.29:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo dvicakkhu? "
msgstr "Who is the person with two eyes? "

msgctxt "an3.29:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tathārūpaṃ cakkhu hoti yathārūpena cakkhunā anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigaccheyya, adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ kareyya; "
msgstr "It’s someone who has the kind of vision that’s needed to acquire more wealth and to increase the wealth they’ve already acquired. "

msgctxt "an3.29:3.3"
msgid "tathārūpampissa cakkhu hoti yathārūpena cakkhunā kusalākusale dhamme jāneyya; "
msgstr "And they have the kind of vision that’s needed to know the difference between skillful and unskillful, blameworthy and blameless, inferior and superior, or qualities on the side of dark and bright. "

msgctxt "an3.29:3.4"
msgid "sāvajjānavajje dhamme jāneyya, hīnappaṇīte dhamme jāneyya, kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāge dhamme jāneyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.29:3.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo dvicakkhu. "
msgstr "This is called a two-eyed person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.29:3.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasminti. "
msgstr "These are the three people found in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.29:4.1"
msgid "Na ceva bhogā tathārūpā, "
msgstr "Neither suitable wealth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:4.2"
msgid "na ca puññāni kubbati; "
msgstr "nor merit do they make. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:4.3"
msgid "Ubhayattha kaliggāho, "
msgstr "They lose on both counts, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:4.4"
msgid "andhassa hatacakkhuno. "
msgstr "those who are blind, with ruined eyes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.29:5.1"
msgid "Athāparāyaṃ akkhāto, "
msgstr "And now the one-eyed "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:5.2"
msgid "Ekacakkhu ca puggalo; "
msgstr "person is explained. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: saṭhoso → sasaṭho (bj) | saṃsaṭṭho (s1-3, km, pts1) | saṭhoti (mr)
msgctxt "an3.29:5.3"
msgid "Dhammādhammena saṭhoso, "
msgstr "By methods good and bad, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:5.4"
msgid "Bhogāni pariyesati. "
msgstr "that devious person seeks wealth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.29:6.1"
msgid "Theyyena kūṭakammena, "
msgstr "Both by fraudulent, thieving deeds, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:6.2"
msgid "musāvādena cūbhayaṃ; "
msgstr "and also by lies, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: saṅghātuṃ → saṃhātuṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.29:6.3"
msgid "Kusalo hoti saṅghātuṃ, "
msgstr "the young man’s skilled at piling up money, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:6.4"
msgid "kāmabhogī ca mānavo; "
msgstr "and enjoying sensual pleasures. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:6.5"
msgid "Ito so nirayaṃ gantvā, "
msgstr "From here they go to hell—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:6.6"
msgid "ekacakkhu vihaññati. "
msgstr "the one-eyed person is ruined. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.29:7.1"
msgid "Dvicakkhu pana akkhāto, "
msgstr "And now the two-eyed is explained, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:7.2"
msgid "seṭṭho purisapuggalo; "
msgstr "the best individual. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:7.3"
msgid "Dhammaladdhehi bhogehi, "
msgstr "Their wealth is earned legitimately, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:7.4"
msgid "uṭṭhānādhigataṃ dhanaṃ. "
msgstr "money acquired by their own hard work. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.130, sc8
msgctxt "an3.29:8.1"
msgid "Dadāti seṭṭhasaṅkappo, "
msgstr "They give with best of intentions, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:8.2"
msgid "abyaggamānaso naro; "
msgstr "that peaceful-hearted person. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:8.3"
msgid "Upeti bhaddakaṃ ṭhānaṃ, "
msgstr "They go to a good place, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:8.4"
msgid "yattha gantvā na socati. "
msgstr "where there is no sorrow. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.29:9.1"
msgid "Andhañca ekacakkhuñca, "
msgstr "The blind and the one-eyed, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:9.2"
msgid "ārakā parivajjaye; "
msgstr "you should avoid from afar. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:9.3"
msgid "Dvicakkhuṃ pana sevetha, "
msgstr "But you should keep the two-eyed close, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:9.4"
msgid "seṭṭhaṃ purisapuggalan”ti. "
msgstr "the best individual.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.29:9.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
